Now all microlibs (which use commonjs exports) can be accessed by a require method.

   var _ = require('underscore'); //returns underscore object

complete rewrite of ender builder
 + uses bundle install if npm version < 1 else uses regular npm install (for rc 1 stuff)
 + removes all depencies except color + uglify js (for faster loading when doing bundling)
 + no longer goes to github for any dependencies (this means you don't have to be connected to the internet to build (assuming you already have NPM installed your desired packages
 + adds new cli api:

   build (or -b): regular build
   async (or -a): creates an async build, which uses script.js to asyncronously load modules from node_modules
   help: explains api

 + cleans up api (much less code, less dependcies loaded into node_modules dir
